## 5. Design Constraints

### Tone & Style
- **Overall Tone:** {{ tone | default("Professional and trustworthy") }}
- **Target Audience Expectations:** Design must resonate with {{ audience }}
- The visual language should communicate that this product solves: {{ problem }}

### Responsive Requirements
- All pages must be fully responsive across Desktop, Tablet, Mobile Landscape, and Mobile Portrait breakpoints.
- Mobile-first content hierarchy: ensure the core value prop and primary CTA are visible without scrolling on mobile.
- Touch targets must be at least 44x44px on mobile breakpoints.
- Images should use Webflow's responsive image settings for performance.

### Interaction & Animation Guidelines
- Use subtle scroll-triggered animations for section reveals (Webflow Interactions 2.0).
- Keep page load animations under 500ms to avoid perceived slowness.
- Hover states on all interactive elements (buttons, cards, links).
- Avoid auto-playing video or heavy animations on mobile.

### Typography & Spacing
- Limit to 2 typefaces maximum (one heading, one body).
- Maintain a consistent spacing scale (8px base grid recommended).
- Ensure text contrast meets WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 minimum for body text).

